This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on August 5, 2009, designates the order of succession for the Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP) in the event that the Director is unable to perform their duties. The designated officials to act as Director in order of succession are the Associate Director (National Security and International Affairs), Associate Director (Technology), Associate Director (Science), and Associate Director (Environment). The memorandum also includes exceptions and revokes a previous memorandum from December 11, 2002. It states that the purpose of the memorandum is to improve the internal management of the executive branch and does not create any enforceable rights or benefits. The Director is authorized to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.